===Etymology===
From {{etyl|nl|en}} {{term|bamboe|lang=nl}}, from {{etyl|pt|en}} {{term|bambu|lang=pt}}, from {{etyl|ms|en}} {{term|bambu|lang=ms}}, from {{etyl|kn|en}} {{term|ಬಂಬು|lang=kn}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/bæmˈbu/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-bamboo.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[grass]] of the [[Poaceae]] family, characterised by its woody, hollow, round, straight, jointed stem, all of which are in the {{taxlink|Bambuseae|tribe|noshow=1}} tribe.
# The wood of the bamboo plant as a material or [[cane]].
# A [[didgeridoo]].
# {{context|slang|lang=en}} A member of the [[British]] [[military]] or [[British East India Company]] who spent so much time in Indonesia, India, or Malaysia that they never went back home.

